[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":254},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F17\u002Fpwa-intro-day1\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F17\u002Fpwa-intro-day1\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F17\u002Fpwa-intro-day1\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F17\u002Fpwa-intro-day1\u002F":232,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F17\u002Fpwa-intro-day1\u002F":241},"\u002Fpwa\u002F20191017\u002F2186080947\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":216,"date":217,"description":218,"extension":219,"lang":220,"meta":221,"navigation":222,"path":223,"readingMinutes":224,"seo":225,"standalone":226,"stem":227,"tags":228,"tldr":229,"updated":217,"url":230,"__hash__":231},"content\u002Fen\u002FPWA\u002Fpwa-intro-day1.md","Day 1 — PWA First Look: Intro","5887580803",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":207},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,35,38,45,54,60,63,67,70,84,87,93,100,106,109,115,118,124,127,133,136,142,145,151,154,160,163,169,172,178,182,185,189,195,202],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"PWA is a steadily maturing web technology. What is it, what's it good for, and why should you care? Let's get into PWA.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"what-is-pwa","What is PWA?",[17,25,26,27,34],{},"PWA was introduced at Google I\u002FO 2016. Quick context — Google I\u002FO is Google's annual developer conference (",[28,29,33],"a",{"href":30,"rel":31},"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FGoogle_I\u002FO",[32],"nofollow","reference","). PWA stands for Progressive Web App. Some people also call it a hybrid app.",[17,36,37],{},"Why did PWA come about? A couple of reasons. One — more and more people use smartphones to browse the web, and to get to a site they need to remember the URL. People are forgetful, so URLs get forgotten and users don't come back. Two — people love installing apps. Just how much? Look at 2017's download numbers:",[17,39,40],{},[41,42],"img",{"alt":43,"src":44},"From \"Global App Market Trends\"","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fv23g42k.png",[17,46,47,48,53],{},"PWA mimics native apps — you can turn a web page into an app icon on your home screen, improve the user experience, and even support offline access. In Google's official handbook ",[28,49,52],{"href":50,"rel":51},"https:\u002F\u002Fdevelopers.google.com\u002Fweb\u002Ffundamentals\u002Fcodelabs\u002Fyour-first-pwapp\u002F",[32],"Your First Progressive Web App",", you'll see a weather-app-style screenshot:",[17,55,56],{},[41,57],{"alt":58,"src":59},"From \"Your First Progressive Web App\"","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqJTvXTg.png",[17,61,62],{},"That's a real PWA — the weather app shown is built entirely with web tech.",[12,64,66],{"id":65},"pwa-in-practice","PWA in practice",[17,68,69],{},"OK enough abstract talk — is there a real-world example? I bet that's what you're thinking.",[17,71,72,73,78,79,83],{},"The Google I\u002FO 2016 official site itself is built with PWA. Try opening ",[28,74,77],{"href":75,"rel":76},"https:\u002F\u002Fevents.google.com\u002Fio2016\u002F",[32],"Google I\u002FO 2016 official site"," on your phone — and importantly, ",[80,81,82],"strong",{},"use Chrome",".",[17,85,86],{},"Open the I\u002FO 2016 site in Chrome on mobile:",[17,88,89],{},[41,90],{"alt":91,"src":92},"Google I\u002FO 2016","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPEQXxkc.png",[17,94,95,96,99],{},"Two ways to add it to your home screen. First — a prompt automatically pops up asking ",[80,97,98],{},"whether to add I\u002FO 2016 to the home screen",":",[17,101,102],{},[41,103],{"alt":104,"src":105},"Add to home screen prompt","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FKySEgbS.png",[17,107,108],{},"Second — manually add it to the home screen:",[17,110,111],{},[41,112],{"alt":113,"src":114},"Add to home screen menu","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FzZrNNsy.png",[17,116,117],{},"When you tap Add, you'll see a confirmation:",[17,119,120],{},[41,121],{"alt":122,"src":123},"Confirm add","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FSoeR8lA.png",[17,125,126],{},"Now you'll see I\u002FO 2016 on your home screen.",[17,128,129],{},[41,130],{"alt":131,"src":132},"PWA created","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FIoeyWcb.png",[17,134,135],{},"What about a site that doesn't support PWA? Let me try Hexschool:",[17,137,138],{},[41,139],{"alt":140,"src":141},"Hexschool","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FM8mkJuQ.png",[17,143,144],{},"You'll notice the \"Add to home screen\" experience is different — no logo, and the name looks like a bookmark:",[17,146,147],{},[41,148],{"alt":149,"src":150},"Add to home screen","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXTOKj5q.png",[17,152,153],{},"The home screen difference is obvious:",[17,155,156],{},[41,157],{"alt":158,"src":159},"Difference","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FfmBjLtX.png",[17,161,162],{},"Even removal is different. A PWA gets removed like an app — really feels native:",[17,164,165],{},[41,166],{"alt":167,"src":168},"Remove app","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FIcTG8Eb.png",[17,170,171],{},"The non-PWA Hexschool one just gets removed like a bookmark:",[17,173,174],{},[41,175],{"alt":176,"src":177},"Remove bookmark","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fzax1IXy.png",[12,179,181],{"id":180},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[17,183,184],{},"This intro series will go hands-on with an actual project so you can feel PWA's power for real. Let's keep going.",[12,186,188],{"id":187},"references","References",[17,190,191],{},[28,192,194],{"href":30,"rel":193},[32],"Google I\u002FO",[17,196,197],{},[28,198,201],{"href":199,"rel":200},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.dgtaipei.tw\u002Fupload\u002Fpdf\u002F%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B%E5%B8%82%E5%A0%B4%E8%AB%96%E5%A3%87-%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E8%A1%8C%E5%8B%95%E6%87%89%E7%94%A8%E5%B8%82%E5%A0%B4%E5%88%86%E6%9E%90_AppAnnie.pdf",[32],"Global App Market Trends (PDF, Mandarin)",[17,203,204],{},[28,205,52],{"href":50,"rel":206},[32],{"title":208,"searchDepth":209,"depth":209,"links":210},"",2,[211,212,213,214,215],{"id":14,"depth":209,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":209,"text":23},{"id":65,"depth":209,"text":66},{"id":180,"depth":209,"text":181},{"id":187,"depth":209,"text":188},"PWA","2019-10-17 09:14:48","PWA is a steadily maturing web technology. What is it, what's it good for, and why bother learning it? Let's get into PWA.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002Fpwa-intro-day1","2",{"title":6,"description":218},false,"en\u002FPWA\u002Fpwa-intro-day1",[216],null,"\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F17\u002Fpwa-intro-day1\u002F","h1q4FLoYA_hlbTDpec5Ts_GFTbIzJD5izB1CSBv13T0",{"newer":233,"older":237},{"url":234,"title":235,"date":236},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fmopcon-2019-day2-recap\u002F","MOPCON 2019 — One Day Recap","2019-10-20 18:02:46",{"url":238,"title":239,"date":240},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F15\u002Fjs-from-zero-extra-closing-thoughts\u002F","RE: Learning JS Life From Zero — Bonus Chapter: Closing Thoughts","2019-10-15 00:00:05",[242,246,250],{"url":243,"title":244,"date":245,"readingMinutes":224},"\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F03\u002Fpwa-hands-on-day6\u002F","Day 6 — PWA First Look: Hands-On With a Real Project","2019-12-03 09:53:48",{"url":247,"title":248,"date":249,"readingMinutes":224},"\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F11\u002F26\u002Fpwa-dev-environment-day5\u002F","Day 5 — PWA First Look: Dev Environment Setup","2019-11-26 09:24:48",{"url":251,"title":252,"date":253,"readingMinutes":224},"\u002Fen\u002Fpwa\u002F2019\u002F11\u002F14\u002Fpwa-architecture-service-workers-day4\u002F","Day 4 — PWA First Look: Architecture (Part 2, Service Workers)","2019-11-14 22:56:48",1784012785273]